" Code="# Define the original file path (provide the file path here)
$OriginalFilePath = $filepath

# Check if the original file exists
if (Test-Path $OriginalFilePath) {
    # Get the directory path of the original file
    $DirectoryPath = [System.IO.Path]::GetDirectoryName($OriginalFilePath)

    # Generate the new file name with the current date
    $CurrentDate = Get-Date -Format "dd-MM-yyyy"
    $NewFileName = "daily summary_$CurrentDate.xlsx"

    # Construct the new file path
    $NewFilePath = Join-Path -Path $DirectoryPath -ChildPath $NewFileName

    # Copy the original file to the new file path
    Copy-Item -Path $OriginalFilePath -Destination $NewFilePath -Force

    # Output the new file path
    $NewFilePath
} else {
    Write-Host "The specified file does not exist."
}

    <osa:InvokeCode PipelineOutput="{x:Null}" sap2010:Annotation.AnnotationText="code to send mail " Code="import smtplib
from email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart
from email.mime.text import MIMEText
from email.mime.base import MIMEBase
from email import encoders

def send_email(sender_email, sender_password, recipient_email, subject, body, attachment_path):
    # Setup the MIME
    message = MIMEMultipart()
    message['From'] = "openrpa10@gmail.com"
    message['To'] = "merinjai02@gmail.com"
    message['Subject'] = "hi test mail"

    # Attach the body to the email
    message.attach(MIMEText(body, 'plain'))

    # Attach the file
    if attachment_path:
        attachment = open(attachment_path, "rb")
        part = MIMEBase('application', 'octet-stream')
        part.set_payload(attachment.read())
        encoders.encode_base64(part)
        part.add_header('Content-Disposition', f"attachment; filename= {attachment_path}")
        message.attach(part)

    # Connect to the SMTP server
    with smtplib.SMTP('smtp.gmail.com', 587) as smtp_server:
        smtp_server.starttls()

        # Login to the SMTP server using sender's credentials
        smtp_server.login(sender_email, sender_password)

        # Send the email
        smtp_server.send_message(message)

# Example usage
sender_email = 'openrpa10@gmail.com'  # Update with your Gmail address
sender_password = 'qydqqowothxurkwt'  # Update with your Gmail app password or OAuth token
recipient_email = 'merinjai02@example.com'  # Update with recipient's email address
subject = 'Daily summary'
body = 'This is a test email with attachment sent from OpenRPA using Python.'
attachment_path = path  # Replace with the path to your Excel file
